      "writtenOn": "2020-03-16T20:23:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Signal codes should be dealt with the same way as or similarly to the way we deal with them on Linux. See ExceptionSnapshotLinux::ReadSiginfo.\n\nYou’d think that some of that may be share-able, but probably only with a bit of #ifdefing, and maybe not at all given that you’ll be running in-process. But you can use it as a guide. However, note that the way that a kernel populates the fields of siginfo_t is very OS-specific, and what Linux does won’t match what xnu does 100%.",
      "revId": "cf2c0b2eb9ec889ba0187a92e30b70db5da22388",
