      "message": "We should probably be using native types for these, although they’ll need a conversion on the way out in order to adhere to the ExceptionSnapshot interface, so it’s not such a huge deal.\n\nHowever, at whatever the point of conversion is, we should be checking to make sure statically that either the source and destination types are compatible (no data loss possible, even in theory), or if not to make sure that the source value fits into the target type at runtime (no data loss in practice).",
